#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Other OS Resources"
msgstr "其他操作系统资源"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:891
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are a number of resources focused on other operating systems that may "
"be useful for FreeBSD users:"
msgstr "有许多针对其他操作系统的资源可能对FreeBSD用户有用："

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:893
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"https://wiki.winehq.org/[The WINE Wiki] has a wealth of information on using"
" WINE, much of which is applicable across many of WINE's supported operating"
" systems."
msgstr ""
"https://wiki.winehq.org/【WINE Wiki】上有大量关于使用WINE的信息，其中很多适用于WINE支持的多个操作系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:894
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Similarly, the documentation available from other OS projects can also be of"
" good value. https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/wine[The WINE page] on the"
" Arch Linux Wiki is a particularly good example, although some of the "
"\"Third-party applications\" (i.e., \"companion applications\") are "
"obviously not available on FreeBSD."
msgstr ""
"同样，其他操作系统项目提供的文档也可能非常有价值。Arch Linux "
"Wiki上的https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/wine[WINE页面]是一个特别好的例子，尽管一些“第三方应用程序”（即“伴侣应用程序”）显然在FreeBSD上不可用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/wine/_index.adoc:894
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Finally, Codeweavers (a developer of a commercial version of WINE) is an "
"active upstream contributor. Oftentimes answers to questions in "
"https://www.codeweavers.com/support/forums[their support forum] can be of "
"aid in troubleshooting problems with the open source version of WINE."
msgstr ""
"最后，Codeweavers（一家商业版WINE的开发者）是一个积极的上游贡献者。在https://www.codeweavers.com/support/forums[他们的支持论坛]中，对于解决开源版本WINE的问题，经常可以找到有帮助的答案。"
